Hello! Imagine the whole of China is like a giant, very big school with millions of students.

In London, you have a Mayor and a City Council who help make rules for your city, right? Well, China is so huge that it needs a special group of people to make rules for the whole country. That group is called the **National People's Congress**.

Here is how it works, in a simple way:

1.  **The Big Meeting:** Once a year, hundreds of people from all over China come together to a very big hall in Beijing. It's like a giant school assembly, but instead of students, it's grown-ups who were chosen by people in their towns and cities.
2.  **Listening and Talking:** These people listen to what is happening in China. They talk about big things, like building new bridges, making sure everyone has good schools, or helping people stay healthy.
3.  **Making the Rules:** After they talk, they vote (like raising your hand in class) to decide on the most important rules for the country. They also choose the leaders who will help run the country, kind of like how a class might choose a monitor to help the teacher.

So, you can think of the National People's Congress as the **biggest team of helpers** in China who meet once a year to make sure the whole country is happy, safe, and growing well! [end of text]


